  "texts": [
    "In Sect. 3, the complete working methodology of proposed architecture is presented in detail.",
    "CNN vs ViT vs CCTThe ViT is a machine learning model for image classification that utilizes a transformer-based architecture on patches of the image.",
    "It was first introduced in a research paper titled \"An Image is Worth 16 × 16 Words\" presented at the ICLR 2021 conference by Neil Houlsby and colleagues [24].",
    "The model is pre-trained on large image datasets such as Ima-geNet-21k and ImageNet [56], and employs a mechanism of attention seeking, which allows it to assign varying levels of importance to different parts of the input data.",
    "The ViT model is composed of multiple self-attention layers, similar to those used in natural language processing, which hold great potential for use in various data modalities."
  ],
